author: felicity
msg: d'oh!  the problem with the rule tests ended up to be really simple after
running around in circles then staring at the rules for a while.  since the
tests are !~ instead of =~, the regression test has to be inverse from the
normal setting as well.  "fail" means that the date is valid and "ok" means
the date is invalid, which is of course briliantly obvious if you think about
it.  also, T_INVALID_DATE won't fail on "24:00", but T_INVALID_DATE2 will,
which is a better rule anyway imo, so change to using that for testing. <sigh>
